{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/quickstart.md#overview", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/quickstart.md", "anchor": "overview", "breadcrumb": "Quickstart > Overview", "level": 2, "position": 0, "text": "> Get started with the Python or TypeScript Agent SDK to build AI agents that work autonomously\n\nUse the Agent SDK to build an AI agent that reads your code, finds bugs, and fixes them, all without manual intervention.\n\nWhat you'll do:\n\n1. Set up a project with the Agent SDK\n2. Create a file with some buggy code\n3. Run an agent that finds and fixes the bugs automatically", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": null, "external_links": []}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/quickstart.md#prerequisites", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/quickstart.md", "anchor": "prerequisites", "breadcrumb": "Quickstart > Prerequisites", "level": 2, "position": 1, "text": "- Node.js 18+ or Python 3.10+\n- An Anthropic account (sign up here)", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": null, "external_links": ["https://platform.claude.com/"]}
