{"kind": "codeblock", "id": "e7dfc6204adff684", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/quickstart.md#setup", "position": 2, "language": "bash", "text": "uv init && uv add claude-agent-sdk", "preceding_paragraph": "uv Python package manager is a fast Python package manager that handles virtual environments automatically:", "in_codegroup": false, "codegroup_id": null}
{"kind": "codeblock", "id": "7c5b5d10388ea829", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/quickstart.md#setup", "position": 3, "language": "bash", "text": "python3 -m venv .venv && source .venv/bin/activate\npip3 install claude-agent-sdk", "preceding_paragraph": "Create a virtual environment first, then install:", "in_codegroup": false, "codegroup_id": null}
{"kind": "callout", "id": "3bd39549b7726783", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/quickstart.md#setup", "position": 0, "callout_kind": "note", "text": "The TypeScript SDK bundles a native Claude Code binary for your platform as an optional dependency, so you don't need to install Claude Code separately."}
{"kind": "codeblock", "id": "9b0698bc13d484d1", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/quickstart.md#setup", "position": 4, "language": "bash", "text": "ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=your-api-key", "preceding_paragraph": "Get an API key from the Claude Console, then create a `.env` file in your project directory:", "in_codegroup": false, "codegroup_id": null}
{"kind": "callout", "id": "c939416bb46f640e", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/quickstart.md#setup", "position": 1, "callout_kind": "note", "text": "Unless previously approved, Anthropic does not allow third party developers to offer claude.ai login or rate limits for their products, including agents built on the Claude Agent SDK. Please use the API key authentication methods described in this document instead."}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/quickstart.md#setup", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/quickstart.md", "anchor": "setup", "breadcrumb": "Quickstart > Setup", "level": 2, "position": 2, "text": "Create a project folder\n\nCreate a new directory for this quickstart:\n\nFor your own projects, you can run the SDK from any folder; it will have access to files in that directory and its subdirectories by default.\n\nInstall the SDK\n\nInstall the Agent SDK package for your language:\n\nTypeScript\n\nPython (uv)\n\nuv Python package manager is a fast Python package manager that handles virtual environments automatically:\n\nPython (pip)\n\nCreate a virtual environment first, then install:\n\nSet your API key\n\nGet an API key from the Claude Console, then create a `.env` file in your project directory:\n\nThe SDK also supports authentication via third-party API providers:\n\n- Amazon Bedrock: set `CLAUDE_CODE_USE_BEDROCK=1` environment variable and configure AWS credentials\n- Google Vertex AI: set `CLAUDE_CODE_USE_VERTEX=1` environment variable and configure Google Cloud credentials\n- Microsoft Azure: set `CLAUDE_CODE_USE_FOUNDRY=1` environment variable and configure Azure credentials\n\nSee the setup guides for Bedrock, Vertex AI, or Azure AI Foundry for details.", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": null, "external_links": ["http://claude.ai", "https://docs.astral.sh/uv/", "https://platform.claude.com/"]}
{"kind": "codeblock", "id": "3e9fcdf433ec8ef3", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/quickstart.md#create-a-buggy-file", "position": 0, "language": "python", "text": "def calculate_average(numbers):\n    total = 0\n    for num in numbers:\n        total += num\n    return total / len(numbers)\n\ndef get_user_name(user):\n    return user[\"name\"].upper()", "preceding_paragraph": "This quickstart walks you through building an agent that can find and fix bugs in code. First, you need a file with some intentional bugs for the agent to fix. Create `utils.py` in the `my-agent` directory and paste the following code:", "in_codegroup": false, "codegroup_id": null}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/quickstart.md#create-a-buggy-file", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/quickstart.md", "anchor": "create-a-buggy-file", "breadcrumb": "Quickstart > Create a buggy file", "level": 2, "position": 3, "text": "This quickstart walks you through building an agent that can find and fix bugs in code. First, you need a file with some intentional bugs for the agent to fix. Create `utils.py` in the `my-agent` directory and paste the following code:\n\nThis code has two bugs:\n\n1. `calculate_average([])` crashes with division by zero\n2. `get_user_name(None)` crashes with a TypeError", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": null, "external_links": []}
{"kind": "codeblock", "id": "b07520ad64412413", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/quickstart.md#build-an-agent-that-finds-and-fixes-bugs", "position": 0, "language": "python", "text": "import asyncio\nfrom claude_agent_sdk import query, ClaudeAgentOptions, AssistantMessage, ResultMessage\n\nasync def main():\n    # Agentic loop: streams messages as Claude works\n    async for message in query(\n        prompt=\"Review utils.py for bugs that would cause crashes. Fix any issues you find.\",\n        options=ClaudeAgentOptions(\n            allowed_tools=[\"Read\", \"Edit\", \"Glob\"],  # Tools Claude can use\n            permission_mode=\"acceptEdits\",  # Auto-approve file edits\n        ),\n    ):\n        # Print human-readable output\n        if isinstance(message, AssistantMessage):\n            for block in message.content:\n                if hasattr(block, \"text\"):\n                    print(block.text)  # Claude's reasoning\n                elif hasattr(block, \"name\"):\n                    print(f\"Tool: {block.name}\")  # Tool being called\n        elif isinstance(message, ResultMessage):\n            print(f\"Done: {message.subtype}\")  # Final result\n\nasyncio.run(main())", "preceding_paragraph": "Create `agent.py` if you're using the Python SDK, or `agent.ts` for TypeScript:", "in_codegroup": true, "codegroup_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/quickstart.md#build-an-agent-that-finds-and-fixes-bugs::cg1"}
{"kind": "codeblock", "id": "87e0de83e5e46d59", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/quickstart.md#build-an-agent-that-finds-and-fixes-bugs", "position": 1, "language": "typescript", "text": "import { query } from \"@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk\";\n\n// Agentic loop: streams messages as Claude works\nfor await (const message of query({\n  prompt: \"Review utils.py for bugs that would cause crashes. Fix any issues you find.\",\n  options: {\n    allowedTools: [\"Read\", \"Edit\", \"Glob\"], // Tools Claude can use\n    permissionMode: \"acceptEdits\" // Auto-approve file edits\n  }\n})) {\n  // Print human-readable output\n  if (message.type === \"assistant\" && message.message?.content) {\n    for (const block of message.message.content) {\n      if (\"text\" in block) {\n        console.log(block.text); // Claude's reasoning\n      } else if (\"name\" in block) {\n        console.log(`Tool: ${block.name}`); // Tool being called\n      }\n    }\n  } else if (message.type === \"result\") {\n    console.log(`Done: ${message.subtype}`); // Final result\n  }\n}", "preceding_paragraph": "Create `agent.py` if you're using the Python SDK, or `agent.ts` for TypeScript:", "in_codegroup": true, "codegroup_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/quickstart.md#build-an-agent-that-finds-and-fixes-bugs::cg1"}
{"kind": "callout", "id": "03a81ee8d714ab07", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/quickstart.md#build-an-agent-that-finds-and-fixes-bugs", "position": 0, "callout_kind": "note", "text": "This example uses streaming to show progress in real-time. If you don't need live output (e.g., for background jobs or CI pipelines), you can collect all messages at once. See Streaming vs. single-turn mode for details."}
{"kind": "codeblock", "id": "2e37fbf22ea32509", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/quickstart.md#run-your-agent", "position": 0, "language": "bash", "text": "python3 agent.py", "preceding_paragraph": "Python", "in_codegroup": false, "codegroup_id": null}
{"kind": "codeblock", "id": "87f3988f5d4e5a31", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/quickstart.md#run-your-agent", "position": 1, "language": "bash", "text": "npx tsx agent.ts", "preceding_paragraph": "TypeScript", "in_codegroup": false, "codegroup_id": null}
{"kind": "callout", "id": "8979adaac9100312", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/quickstart.md#run-your-agent", "position": 0, "callout_kind": "note", "text": "If you see \"API key not found\", make sure you've set the `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` environment variable in your `.env` file or shell environment. See the full troubleshooting guide for more help."}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/quickstart.md#run-your-agent", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/quickstart.md", "anchor": "run-your-agent", "breadcrumb": "Quickstart > Build an agent that finds and fixes bugs > Run your agent", "level": 3, "position": 5, "text": "Your agent is ready. Run it with the following command:\n\nPython\n\nTypeScript\n\nAfter running, check `utils.py`. You'll see defensive code handling empty lists and null users. Your agent autonomously:\n\n1. Read `utils.py` to understand the code\n2. Analyzed the logic and identified edge cases that would crash\n3. Edited the file to add proper error handling\n\nThis is what makes the Agent SDK different: Claude executes tools directly instead of asking you to implement them.", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/quickstart.md#build-an-agent-that-finds-and-fixes-bugs", "external_links": []}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/quickstart.md#try-other-prompts", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/quickstart.md", "anchor": "try-other-prompts", "breadcrumb": "Quickstart > Build an agent that finds and fixes bugs > Try other prompts", "level": 3, "position": 6, "text": "Now that your agent is set up, try some different prompts:\n\n- `\"Add docstrings to all functions in utils.py\"`\n- `\"Add type hints to all functions in utils.py\"`\n- `\"Create a README.md documenting the functions in utils.py\"`", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/quickstart.md#build-an-agent-that-finds-and-fixes-bugs", "external_links": []}
{"kind": "codeblock", "id": "dd7564204c2946d7", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/quickstart.md#customize-your-agent", "position": 0, "language": "python", "text": "options = ClaudeAgentOptions(\n    allowed_tools=[\"Read\", \"Edit\", \"Glob\", \"WebSearch\"], permission_mode=\"acceptEdits\"\n)", "preceding_paragraph": "Add web search capability:", "in_codegroup": true, "codegroup_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/quickstart.md#customize-your-agent::cg2"}
{"kind": "codeblock", "id": "3cf98e38af04664a", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/quickstart.md#customize-your-agent", "position": 1, "language": "typescript", "text": "const _ = {\n  options: {\n    allowedTools: [\"Read\", \"Edit\", \"Glob\", \"WebSearch\"],\n    permissionMode: \"acceptEdits\"\n  }\n};", "preceding_paragraph": "Add web search capability:", "in_codegroup": true, "codegroup_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/quickstart.md#customize-your-agent::cg2"}
{"kind": "codeblock", "id": "0b4100b52643e043", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/quickstart.md#customize-your-agent", "position": 2, "language": "python", "text": "options = ClaudeAgentOptions(\n    allowed_tools=[\"Read\", \"Edit\", \"Glob\"],\n    permission_mode=\"acceptEdits\",\n    system_prompt=\"You are a senior Python developer. Always follow PEP 8 style guidelines.\",\n)", "preceding_paragraph": "Give Claude a custom system prompt:", "in_codegroup": true, "codegroup_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/quickstart.md#customize-your-agent::cg3"}
{"kind": "codeblock", "id": "31cf5c1331b2a8ce", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/quickstart.md#customize-your-agent", "position": 3, "language": "typescript", "text": "const _ = {\n  options: {\n    allowedTools: [\"Read\", \"Edit\", \"Glob\"],\n    permissionMode: \"acceptEdits\",\n    systemPrompt: \"You are a senior Python developer. Always follow PEP 8 style guidelines.\"\n  }\n};", "preceding_paragraph": "Give Claude a custom system prompt:", "in_codegroup": true, "codegroup_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/quickstart.md#customize-your-agent::cg3"}
{"kind": "codeblock", "id": "5f644bc9ef3abd5f", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/quickstart.md#customize-your-agent", "position": 4, "language": "python", "text": "options = ClaudeAgentOptions(\n    allowed_tools=[\"Read\", \"Edit\", \"Glob\", \"Bash\"], permission_mode=\"acceptEdits\"\n)", "preceding_paragraph": "Run commands in the terminal:", "in_codegroup": true, "codegroup_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/quickstart.md#customize-your-agent::cg4"}
{"kind": "codeblock", "id": "50d02339e2b4f235", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/quickstart.md#customize-your-agent", "position": 5, "language": "typescript", "text": "const _ = {\n  options: {\n    allowedTools: [\"Read\", \"Edit\", \"Glob\", \"Bash\"],\n    permissionMode: \"acceptEdits\"\n  }\n};", "preceding_paragraph": "Run commands in the terminal:", "in_codegroup": true, "codegroup_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/quickstart.md#customize-your-agent::cg4"}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/quickstart.md#customize-your-agent", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/quickstart.md", "anchor": "customize-your-agent", "breadcrumb": "Quickstart > Build an agent that finds and fixes bugs > Customize your agent", "level": 3, "position": 7, "text": "You can modify your agent's behavior by changing the options. Here are a few examples:\n\nAdd web search capability:\n\nGive Claude a custom system prompt:\n\nRun commands in the terminal:\n\nWith `Bash` enabled, try: `\"Write unit tests for utils.py, run them, and fix any failures\"`", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/quickstart.md#build-an-agent-that-finds-and-fixes-bugs", "external_links": []}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/quickstart.md#build-an-agent-that-finds-and-fixes-bugs", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/quickstart.md", "anchor": "build-an-agent-that-finds-and-fixes-bugs", "breadcrumb": "Quickstart > Build an agent that finds and fixes bugs", "level": 2, "position": 4, "text": "Create `agent.py` if you're using the Python SDK, or `agent.ts` for TypeScript:\n\nThis code has three main parts:\n\n1. `query`: the main entry point that creates the agentic loop. It returns an async iterator, so you use `async for` to stream messages as Claude works. See the full API in the Python or TypeScript SDK reference.\n2. `prompt`: what you want Claude to do. Claude figures out which tools to use based on the task.\n3. `options`: configuration for the agent. This example uses `allowedTools` to pre-approve `Read`, `Edit`, and `Glob`, and `permissionMode: \"acceptEdits\"` to auto-approve file changes. Other options include `systemPrompt`, `mcpServers`, and more. See all options for Python or TypeScript.\n\nThe `async for` loop keeps running as Claude thinks, calls tools, observes results, and decides what to do next. Each iteration yields a message: Claude's reasoning, a tool call, a tool result, or the final outcome. The SDK handles the orchestration (tool execution, context management, retries) so you just consume the stream. The loop ends when Claude finishes the task or hits an error.\n\nThe message handling inside the loop filters for human-readable output. Without filtering, you'd see raw message objects including system initialization and internal state, which is useful for debugging but noisy otherwise.", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": null, "external_links": []}
