{"kind": "tablerow", "id": "32ea6166d94dbd6f", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/quickstart.md#key-concepts", "position": 0, "table_position": 1, "headers": ["mode", "behavior", "use case"], "cells": ["`acceptEdits`", "Auto-approves file edits and common filesystem commands, asks for other actions", "Trusted development workflows"]}
{"kind": "tablerow", "id": "c850fd50dccdf3bc", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/quickstart.md#key-concepts", "position": 1, "table_position": 1, "headers": ["mode", "behavior", "use case"], "cells": ["`dontAsk`", "Denies anything not in `allowedTools`", "Locked-down headless agents"]}
{"kind": "tablerow", "id": "8f878c0035c75882", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/quickstart.md#key-concepts", "position": 2, "table_position": 1, "headers": ["mode", "behavior", "use case"], "cells": ["`auto` (TypeScript only)", "A model classifier approves or denies each tool call", "Autonomous agents with safety guardrails"]}
{"kind": "tablerow", "id": "66e057846d68b364", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/quickstart.md#key-concepts", "position": 3, "table_position": 1, "headers": ["mode", "behavior", "use case"], "cells": ["`bypassPermissions`", "Runs every tool without prompts", "Sandboxed CI, fully trusted environments"]}
{"kind": "tablerow", "id": "7d8077193a34af61", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/quickstart.md#key-concepts", "position": 4, "table_position": 1, "headers": ["mode", "behavior", "use case"], "cells": ["`default`", "Requires a `canUseTool` callback to handle approval", "Custom approval flows"]}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/quickstart.md#key-concepts", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/quickstart.md", "anchor": "key-concepts", "breadcrumb": "Quickstart > Key concepts", "level": 2, "position": 8, "text": "Tools control what your agent can do:\n\nPermission modes control how much human oversight you want:\n\nThe example above uses `acceptEdits` mode, which auto-approves file operations so the agent can run without interactive prompts. If you want to prompt users for approval, use `default` mode and provide a `canUseTool` callback that collects user input. For more control, see Permissions.", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": null, "external_links": []}
{"kind": "codeblock", "id": "67982eb6d566a917", "section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/quickstart.md#api-error-thinkingtypeenabled-is-not-supported-for-this-model", "position": 0, "language": "text", "text": "API Error: 400 {\"type\":\"invalid_request_error\",\"message\":\"\\\"thinking.type.enabled\\\" is not supported for this model. Use \\\"thinking.type.adaptive\\\" and \\\"output_config.effort\\\" to control thinking behavior.\"}", "preceding_paragraph": "Claude Opus 4.7 replaces `thinking.type.enabled` with `thinking.type.adaptive`. Older Agent SDK versions fail with the following API error when you select `claude-opus-4-7`:", "in_codegroup": false, "codegroup_id": null}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/quickstart.md#api-error-thinkingtypeenabled-is-not-supported-for-this-model", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/quickstart.md", "anchor": "api-error-thinkingtypeenabled-is-not-supported-for-this-model", "breadcrumb": "Quickstart > Troubleshooting > API error `thinking.type.enabled` is not supported for this model", "level": 3, "position": 10, "text": "Claude Opus 4.7 replaces `thinking.type.enabled` with `thinking.type.adaptive`. Older Agent SDK versions fail with the following API error when you select `claude-opus-4-7`:\n\nUpgrade to Agent SDK v0.2.111 or later to use Opus 4.7.", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/quickstart.md#troubleshooting", "external_links": []}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/quickstart.md#troubleshooting", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/quickstart.md", "anchor": "troubleshooting", "breadcrumb": "Quickstart > Troubleshooting", "level": 2, "position": 9, "text": "", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": null, "external_links": []}
{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/quickstart.md#next-steps", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/quickstart.md", "anchor": "next-steps", "breadcrumb": "Quickstart > Next steps", "level": 2, "position": 11, "text": "Now that you've created your first agent, learn how to extend its capabilities and tailor it to your use case:\n\n- Permissions: control what your agent can do and when it needs approval\n- Hooks: run custom code before or after tool calls\n- Sessions: build multi-turn agents that maintain context\n- MCP servers: connect to databases, browsers, APIs, and other external systems\n- Hosting: deploy agents to Docker, cloud, and CI/CD\n- Example agents: see complete examples: email assistant, research agent, and more", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": null, "external_links": ["https://github.com/anthropics/claude-agent-sdk-demos"]}
